                            <comment id="13707043" author="enigmacurry" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 16:03:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the example above, the speculative_retry value didn&apos;t actually get set. I&apos;ll open a separate issue for this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT: Actually, I think this is just that the CLI doesn&apos;t understand cql3 tables. I opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5750&quot; title=&quot;CLI can show bad DESCRIBE for CQL3 CF if given the CF explicitly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5750&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5750&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to save some else this same confusion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13708144" author="iamaleksey" created="Sun, 14 Jul 2013 22:53:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch adds the missing default_time_to_live, speculative_retry, and memtable_flush_period_in_ms to DESCRIBE output.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13708218" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 15 Jul 2013 03:19:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
